
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ispell-wrapper` yek ravesh baraye estefade az `ispell` az dakhel barname-haye digar, mesle `Emacs` ast. In dastoor komak mikonad ta eshtebahat emlaei ra peyda va dorost konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor.
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Namayesh version dastoor.
    🔹 `< file` --> 📝 Check kardane emlaye matne dakhele yek file.
    🔹 `| ispell-wrapper` --> ✍️ Payvand zadane khorooji yek dastoor digar be ispell-wrapper baraye baresiye emlaei.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ispell-wrapper --help

    🔹 Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor `ispell-wrapper`.

    $ cat myfile.txt | ispell-wrapper

    🔹 Baresiye emlaye matne dakhele `myfile.txt` ba estefade az `ispell-wrapper`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ echo "in matn eshtbah emlaei darad." | ispell-wrapper

    🔹 Dastoor emlaye matn ra baresi mikonad va eshtebahat ra neshon midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ispell-wrapper` command provides a way to use `ispell` from within other programs, such as `Emacs`.  It helps to find and correct spelling errors.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Show command help.
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Show command version.
    🔹 `< file` --> 📝 Spell-check the text in a file.
    🔹 `| ispell-wrapper` --> ✍️ Pipe the output of another command to ispell-wrapper for spell checking.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ispell-wrapper --help

    🔹 Show the help message for the `ispell-wrapper` command.

    $ cat myfile.txt | ispell-wrapper

    🔹 Spell-check the text in `myfile.txt` using `ispell-wrapper`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ echo "this sentense has a speling misteke." | ispell-wrapper

    🔹 The command checks the spelling of the text and displays the errors.
